Don’t do jump cuts! This when cut aways come in handy. Pay more attention to sound balance and camera angles – 45 degree rule, make use of different shot sizes

Your commentary James feels unplanned, as if you did it as you were watching it for the first or second time. There is some description of the technical aspects including shots and sound design but there is no analysis of implied readings or meanings. There is a great opportunity to talk about costume that is not taken up. It's actually a very weak clip to analyse in terms of cinematic language, there is very little to read.

You can do much better than this. Plan better, choose earlier, analyse deeper what the impact of technical decisions might be.
Excellent work. You have displayed some good use of manipulating images and a firm grasp of the Pixlr software.

Drew, you cover all of the basic requirements of the brief but there's a worrying lack of detail. You focus a lot on the campaign which is good, but you don't really do enough to focus on the role of the video.

You could set the purpose more clearly, and link the techniques used to this, to ensure a proper discussion of effectiveness. Also, with this topic, there is the chance to really assess whether the techniques impact negatively, as the video raised massive controversy worldwide, and also you could ask the question, do youtube views count as success? Did the video succeed really? More detail needed.

You are not far from a merit grade, and hope you resubmit with these issues covered.

Bethan, this is really close to a merit. The stuff on dreams is really good, but overall it's lacking in reading.

You provide good context at the start of the clip and describe the technical nature of the clip really well. There's good analysis of editing, technically, but overall it lacks an analytical edge, regarding what it means for a viewer, how a viewer is made to feel and what the effects of these techniques are.

The lighting and colour analysis is good, and is close to being merit level, but you need more clarity on how this affects viewers - particularly when the camera leads us through the door before Dorothy, and the impact of seeing Dorothy struggle against the tornado, with little editing, before being knocked out. Your structure and content to analyse was really good, just needed more analysis.
Excellent work. You use of Pixlr software for adjusting the skin image was well blended in to match the surrounding area.

This was a good piece of work Rebecca, but sadly lacking in detail to make it a merit or higher. 

You made good use of technical language, handled technical issues competently, made some good points regarding music, other families with autistic children benefitting but never really took it further. You could have made more of the light at the end of the tunnel, why they change channels, why they use celebrities etc, and also the intended audience.

Some good understanding and description but not enough analysis.

Ryan, there is some great description here, but very little analysis in terms of readings or implied meanings. There are ample opportunities in such a famous clip, and technically, you break it down very clearly and accurately. You start to analyse body movement really well, but it doesn't really go anywhere meaningful beyond an observation.

The analysis you provide for the narrative aspects are superb, but that is not the task. The task is cinematic language and you also miss the chance to talk about the auteur aspects. You can do much better than this.

You describe the scene really well and cover all the technical aspects, despite misunderstanding the nature of auteur theory.

The work on sound and aligning it to image is really good, but overall there is a lack of analysis. You understand the techniques but never seek to look for implied meaning or readings beyond simple observations. You also don't discuss the use of comedy, which is a shame as it is clearly an action/comedy film.

Your semiotic analysis starts well but you don't link ideas, so you describe the signifiers and somewhat, the signifiers but never explain how they work together so the audience understands the intended reading and symbolism. There is also a chance missed regarding the Supercop DVD, because it works even if you haven't seen the film before.

Overall, a good attempt at deconstruction, just lacking in analysis.

There is some really good description of techniques here, and some decent analysis, particularly around colour palette, but there's very little else to warrant a higher grade. You reference the brief well but are let down by poor spelling and grammar on slides, you read from the slides (had no differentiation) and never really discussed the impact of shot selections, tone of voice, music etc.

You clearly grasp the technical aspects but need to do more analysis of their impact, which would have covered purpose and effectiveness criteria.

Your analysis starts really strongly and you cover all the points required for a merit, but it tails off, which stops it being a distinction.

You read meaning very clearly in the colour and lighting elements, it's an excellent analysis of symbolism. The eye level work is superb. The sound analysis is good but could go further. 

The analysis of Fincher is excellent, but you drift from analysing the scene and go for a more general context, along with the Brad Pitt stuff, which is a shame but shows excellent contextual understanding. Overall a really solid piece of work Hayden.

Some really good work here Fran, well done. There is some great work on techniques and impact. For a distinction you need to set out more context at start regarding purpose and then discuss in terms of effectiveness. You could make more of the use of celebrity and there is a small inaccuracy in terms of archive/cutaway.

These are minor, easily fixed elements of what is a really strong and well argued deconstruction.

This is a really strong piece of work Mark. Your technical understanding and use of language is excellent, it's very close to a distinction, let down only by a lack of real analytical detail.

Your auteur, editing, sound and most of your camera analysis is good but you miss opportunities particularly in framing and the relevance of the silhouetted final shot that would have pushed the grade into distinction territory. Overall, great description and content understanding, but good analysis that could have been more thorough for a higher grade.

Reece, you cover all the points required in the brief, but miss out on key points to ensure a higher grade. Your analysis of techniques is not very detailed, and requires more relevance in context to the purpose and the overall effectiveness. You could make more of the importance and status of Children in Need and throughout, set more clearly the purpose, technical delivery and effectiveness of the piece. You are not far from a merit grade as it stands, and I hope you resubmit.

**Resubmitted and Regraded March 2012**

An excellent resubmission Reece, with some care in language, spelling, grammar etc. it could be a distinction report.

The start is excellent and your analysis of sound is superb. The colour reading is great also. The fear symbolism is first class and the acknowledgement of low sound to add suspense is spot on.

What stops it being a distinction is the lack of analysis of meaning and implied readings in the camera work and an over pre-occupation with the Joker, who for a first time audience is not revealed, but hinted at within this scene. Your narrative analysis is sound but you should have applied deeper reading to the significance for audiences in using zooms and tracking shots.

Otherwise, a really solid piece of work Peter.

Robyn, you fulfil the basic criteria, but much more clarity and detail is needed. You provide excellent context for the content, but there's little in the way of real analysis.

What is google chrome fashion for example?
And how do we know it's effective, do youtube views = success?  How is it measured, also, tying in this effectiveness with purpose and techniques is key.

Hope you resubmit for a higher grade, you can easily achieve it.

A really good piece of work Jade, and really close to a distinction. There is some great analysis of techniques, codes and conventions and the nature of a Social Action product. 

For a distinction you could add more context of how these products change attitudes generally, which will allow you to better assess the effectiveness of the video here. You should make more of the use of celebrities and relate the effectiveness to the purpose clearer, otherwise, a superb piece of work.

A really good piece of work, and not far from a distinction.

There are a lot of spelling and grammar errors that hold it back. Your ambitious language use is admirable but you should get it proof read to ensure accuracy of delivery and context.

Your differentiation (not reading from slides) is good and the technical analysis is really strong. You could go further with the analysis, but your use of pain/heartache and comparison is excellent, as is your understanding of the use of direct address. Good slides, good structure.

For a distinction, you need to consider more clearly, how effectiveness is based on purpose and technique, but overall, it's a really solid piece of work. Well done.

So close to a distinction! Really sound piece of work Rebecca. 

Good extrapolation of meaning from images and sound. Excellent understanding of how the context of the story is developed technically. The 'hearts' analysis is superb. Good coverage on set, props etc.

However, what stops it being a distinction is that you never really get beyond the first stage of analysis for much of the clip, as a result missing opportunities to really discuss the black comedy element proposed by the freeze frame/title card moment for example. The boulder analysis is key, but over too quickly which is a shame because you clearly pick up an implied meaning.

Overall though, a really solid piece of work, well done.
